The paper discusses cyber risk management for IoT networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of game theory to design incentive-compatible insurance contracts suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The focus on IoT networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's emphasis on cyber risks and insurance suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CY).
